{"id":14881090,"mediaExerciseId":"96824ca1-4824-4974-9d9d-557e9729d958","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612315,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":238,"solutions":[{"id":6003409,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we have to determine the seniority of the bond to help Renata understand the effect on the coupon rate.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Seniority is about the rank of holders of debt. Some holders have preferences, and if the company goes to bankruptcy, preferences holders will first receive the investments back than other debt holders. Therefore, the higher seniority leads to the higher rank according to preferences to paying the funds back. \n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/bc2ee0ac6003fe600775e1d2c2370007/8db7e941dc4b440ddafaaaf2f5c2c5a5/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/bc2ee0ac6003fe600775e1d2c2370007/8db7e941dc4b440ddafaaaf2f5c2c5a5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"That is an advantage of the bond holder; therefore, the company can provide a lower coupon rate. The disadvantage is if the company will overissue the preference bond, and the current holders will not have this benefit.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":285,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/bc2ee0ac6003fe600775e1d2c2370007/a9254f0760c63dd8511fa21d97261442/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":144,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/bc2ee0ac6003fe600775e1d2c2370007/a9254f0760c63dd85